                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>With more than 11,723 total participants from 2014-2023, the program has made an incredible impact. The results from an AMPATH study published in 2020 revealed that:&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;ul>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>&lt;b>84.4%&lt;/b> of women in chamas deliver their baby in a health facility, compared to 50.4% in a control group&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>&lt;b>75.8%&lt;/b> of women in chamas had a health visit within 48 hours of birth, compared to 38.3% in a control group&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>&lt;b>64%&lt;/b> of women in chamas had 4+ prenatal visits, compared to 37.4% in a control group&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>&lt;b>82% &lt;/b>of women in chamas breastfed exclusively for six months, compared to 47% in a control group&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;/ul>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>In addition to growing participation among women, fathers have also expressed interest in taking part. As a result, AMPATH started separate BabaToto groups to empower men with the same health and parenting education.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                                <separator_239276943__146772958
